quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  2,124,"ňĻRememberňļ when Abraham was tested by his Lord with ňĻcertainňļ commandments, which he fulfilled. God said, ‚ÄúI will certainly make you into a role model for the people.‚ÄĚ Abraham asked, ‚ÄúWhat about my offspring?‚ÄĚ God replied, ‚ÄúMy covenant is not extended to the wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,125,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We made the Sacred House¬†a centre and a sanctuary for the people ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúňĻYou mayňļ take the standing-place of Abraham¬†as a site of prayer.‚ÄĚ And We entrusted Abraham and Ishmael to purify My House for those who circle it, who meditate in it, and who bow and prostrate themselves ňĻin prayerňļ"
  2,126,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said, ‚ÄúMy Lord, make this city ňĻof Meccaňļ secure and provide fruits to its people‚ÄĒthose among them who believe in God and the Last Day.‚ÄĚ He answered, ‚ÄúAs for those who disbelieve, I will let them enjoy themselves for a little while, then I will condemn them to the torment of the Fire. What an evil destination!‚ÄĚ"
  2,127,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham raised the foundation of the House with Ishmael, ňĻboth praying,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Accept ňĻthisňļ from us. You are indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,128,"Our Lord! Make us both ňĻfullyňļ submit to You¬†and from our descendants a nation that will submit to you. Show us our rituals, and turn to us in grace. You are truly the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,129,"Our Lord! Raise from among them a messenger who will recite to them Your revelations, teach them the Book and wisdom, and purify them. Indeed, You ňĻaloneňļ are the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,130,"And who would reject the faith of Abraham except a fool! We certainly chose him in this life, and in the Hereafter he will surely be among the righteous"
  2,131,"When his Lord ordered him, ‚ÄúSubmit ňĻto My Willňļ,‚ÄĚ he responded, ‚ÄúI submit to the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  2,132,"This was the advice of Abraham‚ÄĒas well as Jacob‚ÄĒto his children, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúIndeed, God has chosen for you this faith; so do not die except in ňĻa state of fullňļ submission.‚ÄĚ"
  2,133,"Or did you witness when death came to Jacob? He asked his children, ‚ÄúWho will you worship after my passing?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe will ňĻcontinue toňļ worship your God, the God of your forefathers‚ÄĒAbraham, Ishmael, and Isaac‚ÄĒthe One God. And to Him we ňĻallňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,134,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,135,"The Jews and Christians each say, ‚ÄúFollow our faith to be ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúNo! We follow the faith of Abraham, the upright‚ÄĒwho was not a polytheist.‚ÄĚ"
  2,136,"Say, ňĻO believers,ňļ ‚ÄúWe believe in God and what has been revealed to us; and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord. We make no distinction between any of them. And to God we all submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,137,"So if they believe in what you believe, then they will indeed be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. But if they turn away, they are simply opposed ňĻto the truthňļ. But God will spare you their evil. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,138,This is the ňĻnaturalňļ Way of God. And who is better than God in ordaining a way? And we worship ňĻnone butňļ Him
  2,139,"Say, ‚ÄúWould you dispute with us about God, while He is our Lord and your Lord? We are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. And we are devoted to Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  2,140,"Do you claim that Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants were all Jews or Christians?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWho is more knowledgeable: you or God?‚ÄĚ Who does more wrong than those who hide the testimony they received from God? And God is never unaware of what you do"
  2,141,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done